def findRetweet(tweet):
    if(tweet is not None and tweet[:4] == "RT @"):
        return True
    else:
        return False
    
findRetweetUdf = udf(findRetweet)
In [8]:
import re

def tooManyTags(tweet):
    if(tweet is not None):
        i = 0
        for t in re.finditer('@', tweet):
            i += 1
            if(i > 4):
              return True
        
        for t in re.finditer('#', tweet):
            i += 1
            if(i > 4):
              return True        
        
        return False
    else:
        return False
    
tooManyTagsUdf = udf(tooManyTags)

def plotBarChart(data, ylabel, legendLabel, title, colNames, xkcd_color):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()

    fig.set_size_inches(20.5, 7.5, forward=True)

    N = 10
    ind = np.arange(N)  # the x locations for the groups
    width = 0.27       # the width of the bars

    ax.bar(data[ind, data[colNames[1]][0:10], 0.35,
                    alpha=0.7, color='xkcd:'+xkcd_color,
                    label=legendLabel)
   
    ax.bar(data[colNames[0]][11:20]+2, data[colNames[1]][11:20], 0.35,
                    alpha=0.7, color='xkcd:'+xkcd_color,
                    label=legendLabel)
   
    ax.set_ylabel(ylabel)
    ax.set_title(title)
    ax.legend()

    plt.show()

def plotTimeline(data):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    fig.set_size_inches(20.5, 7.5, forward=True)
    plt.plot(pd.to_datetime(data["conciseDate"]), data["tweetsCount"])
    plt.show()

def plotTimeline2(data1, data2, data3, data4, data5):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    fig.set_size_inches(20.5, 7.5, forward=True)

    frame1 = plt.gca()
    frame1.axes.get_yaxis().set_visible(False)
    
    plt.plot(pd.to_datetime(data1["conciseDate"]), data1["tweetsCount"]+1000, 'r')   
    plt.plot(pd.to_datetime(data2["conciseDate"]), data2["tweetsCount"]+2000, 'b') 
    plt.plot(pd.to_datetime(data3["conciseDate"]), data3["tweetsCount"]+3000, 'g') 
    plt.plot(pd.to_datetime(data4["conciseDate"]), data4["tweetsCount"]+4000, 'y') 
    plt.plot(pd.to_datetime(data5["conciseDate"]), data5["tweetsCount"]+5000, 'm') 
    
    plt.legend(['UChicago', 'Northwestern', 'UMichigan', 'Harvard', 'Princeton'], loc='upper left')
    plt.title('University Twitter Activity over Time')
    plt.show()

from pyspark.sql import Window
from pyspark.sql.functions import rank,sum,col

window = Window.partitionBy("id")

tweets_topusers_distribution = tweets_consolidated\
                                .groupby("id", "screen_name", "classifiedTweet")\
                                .agg(count("classifiedTweet").alias('TweetPerUserCount'))\
                                .orderBy("id", "classifiedTweet")\
                                .withColumn("total", sum(col('TweetPerUserCount')).over(window))\
                                .withColumn("Percent", format_string("%2.2f%%", col('TweetPerUserCount')*100/col('total')))\

from wordcloud import WordCloud
from nltk.corpus import stopwords

def plotWordCloud(tweets_text_target) :
    s=set(stopwords.words('english'))
    s.add('University')
    s.add('Chicago')
    s.add('Northwestern')
    s.add('Michigan')
    s.add('Harvard')
    s.add('Princeton')
    
    tweets_text_array = filter(lambda w: not w in s and w[:5] != 'https' and len(w) > 1,tweets_text_target.split())
    
    tweets_text_array
    
    tweets_text = ' '.join(tweets_text_array)

# Create the wordcloud object
    wordcloud = WordCloud(margin=0).generate(tweets_text)

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 15))  

# Display the generated image:
    plt.title('UChicago - Most discused topics')
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.margins(x=0, y=0)
    plt.show()

import nltk as nltk

def getTriGrams(tweets_text_target):

    s=set(stopwords.words('english'))
    s.add('University')
    s.add('Chicago')
    s.add('Northwestern')
    s.add('Michigan')
    s.add('Harvard')
    s.add('Princeton')

    tweets_text_array = filter(lambda w: not w in s and w[:5] != 'https' and len(w) > 1,tweets_text_target.split())

    tweets_text_array

    tweets_text = ' '.join(tweets_text_array)

    tokens = nltk.word_tokenize(tweets_text)
    tgs = nltk.trigrams(tokens)

    fdist_3 = nltk.FreqDist(tgs)

    fdist_3_df = pd.DataFrame(fdist_3.most_common(), columns=['Word', 'Frequency'])
    
    return fdist_3_df

import nltk as nltk

def getMostFreqWords(textStr):
    words = nltk.tokenize.word_tokenize(textStr)

    stopwords = set(nltk.corpus.stopwords.words('english'))
    stopwords.add('https')

    words = [word for word in words if len(word) > 1]

    words = [word for word in words if word.isalpha()]

    words = [word.lower() for word in words]

    words = [word for word in words if word not in stopwords]


    fdist = nltk.FreqDist(words)

    mCommon = fdist.most_common(10)
    
    return mCommon

def get_features(s):
    width = 3
    s = s.lower()
    s = re.sub(r'[^\w]+', '', s)
    
    return [s[i:i + width] for i in range(len(s) - width + 1)]

    if(univ == 'uchicago'):
        return len(index_uchicago.get_near_dups(Simhash(get_features(t))))
    elif(univ == 'northwestern'):

def plotHistogram(data):        
    dupNums = np.array(data)
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()

    fig.set_size_inches(20.5, 7.5, forward=True)

    (n, bins, patches) = plt.hist(dupNums,  bins=100)
    plt.show()
